59th Defiler<br>
Officer of the Seven Dreams</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uistrahdamtheland.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Istrahd Amtheland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Buffy Bait</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/17/01 12:32:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/istrahd/ist_img.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> true ang true ... lvls mean a lot <p><center><Table width=550 border=0><tr><td valign=top align=center colspan=2><center><img src="http://www.kerinakreation.com/images/sigs/istsig.jpg" border=0 alt="Guild Leader of Dark Whispers"></center></td></tr><tr><td valign=top align=center><i><font color="red"><b>Istrahd V'Zarovich<b></i><br>58th Defiler<br>Dark Whispers<br></font></td><td valign=middle align=center><font size=-1><i>"I am The Ancient, I am The Land. My beginnings are lost in the darkness of the past. I was the warrior, I was good and just. I thundered across the land like the wrath of a just god, but the war years and the killing years wore down my soul as the wind wears stone into sand." - Strahd Von Zarovich</i></font></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujarsek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarsek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/21/01 7:31:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> i feared in skyshrine with 15cha, and with 60. in all my lvls experience i would say that if cha does have affect on ST/fear, it is very little. my friend did have a claw at lvl 15+, and i noticed alot more resists than i tended to get with jarsek. lvl 15 was quite a long time ago so i don't remember what resists with 60cha are back then. If cha does have an affect, its proably more noticeable at lower lvl. <p><img src="http://jalenyawns.homestead.com/files/Jarsig.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unizbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nizbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/21/01 12:39:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> I'm gonna have to agree with Istrahd on this one. I was hunting in HS with a group and I was doing CC. Just felt like certain things were sticking more when I was using the claw. &lt;shrug&gt; Just a feeling though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujedakaskywalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jedaka Skywalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/01 6:06:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> CHA Isn't a big deal,  you'll find some cha modifiers that just happen to be tagging along with the good stats (Claw for example).  Go for the hp/mana stuff if you have good enough int to spend on lowering CHA (Or if your a freak like me wear your resist gear full time)  <br>
<br>
I never noticed a big difference myself,  the one time I was sort of interested in it was when I spent time soloing Frenzied.   <p><img SRC="http://www.seven-dreams.org/images/skywalker.jpg" >
<br> 
Jedaka Bloodreaper<br>
57th Defiler  <br>
Member of Seven Dreams</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujarsek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarsek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/01 7:15:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> only time i wear cha gear is when im having fun charming in lguk or rarely on a raid. resist gear is nice, and i have an assload of it, but i prefer to keep it in my bag and whip it out when i need it on raids. exception to this would be items with huge +resists, like that rare shoulder item off draco, maybe a resistance stone, zland heart cuz its badass regen, belt of dwarf etc. some situations i do wear resist gear when hunting, like when i was hunting monkies for my eye neck i wore diamond crap and a couple other pieces. just because monkies cast all_the_fricken_time for the _love_of_god it sso hard to pull them out of the tunnel. once i had the room broke i stuck my hp gear back on and just sat there, owned anyhting when it spawned. some necros talk about resist gear over hps because it has saved them in certain situations. i think that can be said for both sets, resists and hps. me right now, im not willing to sacrafice huge hps for some resists i use not that often. i might be more inclined if i actually hunted for exp however. anyway, i think i can break 4k full buffs with 3 or 4 new items, that would be a site to see 8P<br>
jarjar <p><img src="http://jalenyawns.homestead.com/files/Jarsig.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unekrotic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nekrotic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/01 9:11:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> Charisma has ZERO effect from experiments I conducted myself.<br>
<br>
I had my charisma down to 1 (the lowest possible you can go, really it should have been something like -20).  I tried out fearing, charming undead, timing them....then switching out to charisma gear (up to 85, at that time didnt bother to go over 100).<br>
<br>
The result? NO DIFFERENCE.  At least nothing significant. Was completely random.  Sometimes my charm would last longer with low charisma, sometimes with high charisma.<br>
<br>
Charm?  No difference.  No statistically significant difference anyways.<br>
<br>
So after this disappointing discovery, I no longer made an effort to keep my charisma low.  Guess what?  No effect on my gameplay.<br>
<br>
The only thing that matters is levels.  The higher level you are, the better your spells are gonna stick.  Period.<br>
<br>
Perhaps a better topic to discuss - is Trepidation really any better than Invoke Fear? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I havent tested this but from just my general use I seem to see no differences.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/neksig.jpg" border="0">

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unekrotic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nekrotic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/22/01 9:14:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> Oh, by the way, I also thought maybe my charisma was too low, that because it was -20 or so it was wrapping around so was actually considered positive charisma...<br>
<br>
So I put on just enough gear to get to a charisma of 2.  And results still showed no improvement in fear or charm success, duration, etc...<br>
<br>
Just to clarify.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/neksig.jpg" border="0">

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolanhazzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan Hazzan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Moderator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/24/01 2:39:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.acinternet.com/leolan/leopic.asp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> Nek, try comparing those results to a CHA of 50 or so.  Or 200.  Or both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>&nbsp;- Leo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unekrotic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nekrotic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/24/01 4:34:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower cha equal better?</span><hr size=1> Yeah Leo, I thought about taking my charisma up to 200 for comparisons, but I'm too ugly and wasnt worth getting all that charisma gear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
